Description: AAA Foundation for Traffic Safety is a not-for-profit organization that conducts research to address growing highway safety issues.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: AAA Foundation for Traffic Safety is a not-for-profit organization that conducts research to address growing highway safety issues. Its aim is to identify traffic safety problems, foster research that seeks solutions, and disseminate information and educational materials. The Foundation has funded over 250 projects designed to discover the causes of traffic crashes, prevent them, and minimize injuries when they do occur. AAA Foundation for Traffic Safety’s studies has shown that understanding the risks of driving and one’s own limitations can prevent crashes. The Foundation’s materials seek to give drivers new skills, sharpen old ones, and change attitudes as the first step to changing behaviors. Additionally, its research is used to create focused, high-impact educational materials for drivers, pedestrians, bicyclists, and road users of all ages. Over time the foundation has expanded its scope and diversified areas of concentration while still focusing on AAA priority issues, including senior safety and mobility, teen driving, road safety, and safety culture.   AAA Foundation for Traffic Safety was founded in 1947 by AAA and is headquartered in Washington, D.C.

DeJarnette Research Systems, Inc. has been known for technical innovation.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Baltimore-Maryland Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: From its inception in 1986, DeJarnette Research Systems, Inc. has been known for technical innovation. In its early years, the company was among the industry leaders in driving standards, such as ACR-NEMA, DICOM, and HL7. Before the advent of DICOM, DeJarnette designed, developed, and manufactured its high  performance, robust, and widely used ACR-NEMA V2.0 interface board called AT/ANSIF and its Medical Network Gateway known as ImageShare 910. Our SureNet assured delivery, "store and forward" with route failover capability, set the standard for early medical network gateway products. The U.S. military and Loral/Siemens selected DeJarnette's ImageShare 910 product as their preferred modality interface for MDIS deployment. DeJarnette’s AN/API (ACR-NEMA Application Programmers Interface) was the first medical imaging software toolkit to support DICOM. With the release of the DICOM standard, we began to focus on deployment of this technology, realizing that a toolkit is not a solution, only a tool. Check out our innovations over the years with AN/API as the core technology. In 2018, as we enter into our 32nd year of operation, DeJarnette is excited to release Entegra+ with XOE, our flexible and easily configurable DICOM and HL7 interface engine. With its extensive product offerings, DeJarnette is dedicated to increasing the efficiency of image management workflow for all types of health care institutions. Our commitment to develop breakthrough applications remains the standard by which future products are being developed and deployed.

Description: Wowd is a real-time search engine for discovering popular content on the web.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Wowd is a real-time search engine for discovering whatâ€™s popular on the web right now. Like other real-time search engines, Wowd delivers information seconds after it appears on the web.  Unlike others, Wowd covers the entire web â€“ any publically available page, from any web site, anywhere, can potentially be included in the Wowd index. Like reference search engines, Wowd performs indexing and ranking of search resultsâ€¦ but it does so in a way that takes into account pages preferred by real users.  Wowd does not use crawlers that mindlessly follow links, filling an index with material that real people would never look at.  Wowd finds and ranks information according to the preferences and interests of real humans. Members of the Wowd user community, the â€œWowd Crowdâ€, determine web page popularity. Traditional search ranking methods are based on how pages link to each other, and this approach has been thoroughly gamed by web site publishers seeking search engine optimization.  People are much better at finding good web pages and avoiding bad ones than computer programs will ever be.  So Wowd taps into this human judgment and gives higher ranking to the pages people choose to visit. Wowd users nominate public pages for inclusion in the index just by visiting them.  When a Wowd Crowd member visits a public web page, it is automatically nominated, and the page is immediately added to the index.  No explicit voting or manual voting is required. The Wowd Crowd is surfing the web twenty-four hours a day, automatically nominating new public web pages for inclusion in the index.  A new page is made available to all Wowd Crowd members just seconds after only one of them finds it.  Thus, Wowd provides a real-time index that spans the entire scope of the human-readable public web. Wowd delivers search results that real people find interesting.  Wowd achieves both comprehensive coverage of the entire web and real-time performance through an innovative, distributed cloud architecture.  Other real-time search engines achieve timeliness at the expense of comprehensiveness.  These services typically index just a handful of sites.  In contrast, Wowd delivers real-time results from the entire web, including all social media sites, all news sites, all blog sites... in fact, all public sites can be included in the Wowd index, provided they are nominated by a member of the Wowd Crowd. Wowd delivers popular and timely information in three ways: (1) a real-time Wowd Hot List of popular web pages that updates live before your eyes; (2) ability to search for specific items and sort results according to popularity or freshness; (3) ability search your own previously visited pages, making it extremely easy to find those pages again. Wowd is a real-time search engine that helps you discover whatâ€™s popular on the web right now.  Wowdâ€™s unique approach is to run as a web browser application, eliminating the need to share personal information with centralized servers.  Wowd protects your privacy.  Wowd does not collect personally identifiable information and does not share your search history or browsing history with anyone, including Wowd, Inc. In summary, Wowd is a great way to find out what real people are talking about, right now, on the web.
Industry Groups: Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Other

Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: UJober is a freelance marketplace that connects buyers and sellers. Initially UJober launched in August 2016 as a video interviewing job portal but in October 2021 was rebranded as a freelance marketplace. UJober is owned by MooreSuccess Inc. a for profit company located in Chicago, Illinois. History UJober was founded in 2016 as a video interviewing job portal by James Moore. Starting off the site was built on Larvel and was custom developed. As a Human Resource Executive Moore wanted to streamline the hiring process allowing for employers to video interview candidates to save time. But, to also allow job seekers the ability to get a new job without having to take time off from work. The site was decommissioned when Covid brought about the increased usage of Zoom which reduced the sites usefulness. In October 2021 UJober relaunched as a freelance marketplace. James Moore seeing the effects Covid caused on the job market he decided to repurpose the site to still be useful for both employers and employees. Company UJober is owned and operated by privately held MooreSuccess Inc. The company is headquartered in Chicago, Illinois. The site is a freelance marketplace that connects buyers and sellers allowing sellers to post digital products and services Freelance Marketplace A freelance marketplace allows for buyers and sellers to collectively come together to partner on a project or projects. The freelancer can either list their service(s) outright or the buyer can post a request and allow freelancers to apply/bid on the project. Similar sites would include Fiverr, Upwork, Freelancer, and People Per Hour.

Ocean County Library, a public library system that connects people, builds community, and transforms lives through the power of information.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Ocean County Library is a public library system that connects people, builds community, and transforms lives through the power of information and stories. The library serves as a portal of knowledge and strengthens civic involvement. It provides content that is digital in nature, as well as supporting its residents’ desire for personal growth. Ocean County Library has 21 library locations to serve a population of 575,397 residents in the 32 municipalities that comprise its service area. Each year, the library circulates over 4.3 million books, answers over 2.5 million reference questions, and provides over 11,500 programs and activities for children, young adults, adults and families, and has over 3 million visits to its library system. Ocean County Library’s collection includes over 1.3 million volumes and consists of print books, e-Books, audio books, magazines, music, DVD’s, videogames, and local history materials. It has 76 databases providing access to thousands of journals, research, and online learning materials. The library has over 494 computers available for public use and all of its library locations offer free web access via Wi-Fi. An Ocean County Library card may be used to borrow books and materials at any of its 21 library locations and to access e-Books and online resources either in the library, or from users’ personal computer with internet access, or through the My OCL app available for users’ smartphone, tablet, or other handheld device. Ocean County Library has a reciprocal borrowing agreement with the Burlington County Library and the Monmouth County Library systems which permit its residents to borrow materials from these library systems and permit residents of Burlington and Monmouth counties who belong to their county library system to borrow books and materials from the Ocean County Library. Ocean County Library has received several awards, including recipient of the national medal for museum and library service, Library Journal’s library of the year 2013 special mention, the 2013 New Jersey Library Association’s library service award for trustees, named one of America’s Star Libraries, recipient of the American Library Association John Cotton Dana Library Public Relations Award, and first place in the American Library Association Diversity Fair. Ocean County Library was founded in 1925 and is based in Oceanside, N.Y.
